
[1]idiopathy

   IDIOP'ATHY, n. [Gr. proper, peculiar, and suffering, disease, to
   suffer.]

   1. An original disease in a particular part of the body; a disease
   peculiar to some part of the body and not proceeding from another
   disease.

   2. Peculiar affection.
